      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      314.08,
      214.37,
      327.36
    ],
    "text": "likelihood of recidivism.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      335.15,
      402.19,
      369.48
    ],
    "text": "11. In R v Kien (2000) 116 A Crim R 339 par [17], it was held that:",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldItal",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0,
      15.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      384.88,
      526.16,
      398.16
    ],
    "text": "\u201cadvanced age may be significant to, but not determinative of, the quantum of a",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      405.52,
      162.02,
      418.8
    ],
    "text": "sentence\u201d.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      443.75,
      526.13,
      457.2
    ],
    "text": "12. It is generally recognized that older offenders may present a lower risk of recidivism and,",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      464.7,
      526.28,
      477.98
    ],
    "text": "consequently, may pose less risk to the public than younger offenders. Moreover, a term of",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      485.34,
      526.03,
      498.62
    ],
    "text": "imprisonment may have a more severe impact on an older offender than on a younger",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      506.1,
      526.12,
      519.38
    ],
    "text": "offender, which may suggest that a comparable degree of retribution could, in certain",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      526.74,
      454.18,
      540.02
    ],
    "text": "circumstances, be achieved with a shorter sentence for the former category.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      571.45,
      526.04,
      584.9
    ],
    "text": "13. Nevertheless, it must be emphasized that offences of this nature require sentences that",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      592.38,
      526.3,
      605.66
    ],
    "text": "reflect not only the gravity of the crime but also the societal interest in protecting vulnerable",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      613.02,
      526.34,
      626.3
    ],
    "text": "victims. Therefore, sentencing must strike a careful balance between individual mitigating",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      633.66,
      331.99,
      646.94
    ],
    "text": "circumstances and the broader interests of justice.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      654.55,
      526.09,
      686.33
    ],
    "text": "14. As stated earlier, the appellant was 66 years old at the time of the commission of the",
